=Description=

"The book  includes a political account of the ACTA, set in the international
context of other copyright initiatives including  the UK’s Digital Economy Act,
and Spain’s Ley Sinde. It demonstrates how the same lobbying inputs generated
three different policy outcomes in three different legislatures. It questions the notion of transparency in policy-making and suggests why copyright measures may violate free speech."


